' ============================================================
' NOTES — anchored to where logic actually lives
' ============================================================
note right of PlayState
  Engine root for a running match.
  PlayState OWNS the engine helpers (CollisionManager,
  ScoreManager, HUD, Camera, EntityManager, LevelManager,
  TextureManager, GameMode).
  players[4] and pilotedVehicle[4] are AGGREGATIONS
  (entities themselves are owned by EntityManager).
end note

note right of CampaignMode
  Currently a stub: setupLevels calls
  LevelManager::loadLevel(5, this) which falls into
  loadBossLevel. Procedural-terrain plumbing
  (NoiseProfile / FractalNoise / CampaignLevel)
  is in the spec but not yet implemented in code.
end note

note right of SurvivalLevel
  Spawning is camera-triggered:
  populateLevel1/2/3() registers SpawnRecipes;
  tickSpawnTriggers(camera) fires them when
  cameraRight >= triggerX (max 4 per frame).
  cowardiceReserve enqueues skipped enemies, then
  re-emits them as grudgeful via tickCowardiceStream.
end note

note right of UltimateBoss
  State-pattern with aggregation:
  three pre-built Boss instances live in forms[3];
  currentForm is reseated every formTransitionInterval
  (~12.5s) by transitionForm(). takeDamage delegates to
  the active form so each form has independent HP.
end note

note right of Inventory
  Prototype host: grenadePrototype is the master Grenade*.
  consumeGrenade() returns prototype->clone() and decrements
  grenadeCount. forceKnifeOnly / restoreSavedWeapon handle
  the Mummy transformation (weapon swap is reversible).
end note

note right of SpawnRecipe
  Prototype + Factory + Trigger:
  owns a master Entity prototype, clones it N times when
  the camera reaches triggerX, then sets spawned=true.
end note

note right of DamagableEntity
  State pattern host: currentDamageState* is swapped via
  advanceDamageState():
    exit -> delete -> next() -> swap -> enter.
  Same shape used by Soldier::changeState and
  Enemy::changeAIState.
end note

note right of Direction
  Strategy with prototype:
  LeftDirection / RightDirection answer getXSign(),
  return their opposite from flip(), and a same-type copy
  from clone(). Used by Soldier::facing and FireStream.
end note

note right of Zombie
  Implements Rule of Three (copy ctor / operator= / dtor)
  because it owns a Weapon* — cloned zombies must not share
  the same pistol pointer.
end note

